'''Larmalstone''' or '''larmal''' was a type of expensive rock found only in the [[Roche asteroid field]]. [[Milk/Legends|Milky]] in [[Color/Legends|color]], it was used as a floor covering, as well as to produce statues and other furniture.

[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] had a larmalstone floor in the cul-de-sac leading to their [[Eastport/Legends|Eastport]] [[Solo apartment|apartment]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].

[[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Nek Bwua'tu]] had a larmalstone bust of Admiral [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]] aboard the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] ship [[Admiral Ackbar (Victory-class)|''Admiral Ackbar'']].

A priceless larmal-topped end table was present in the [[Queen Mother's Special Salon]] on [[Hapes/Legends|Hapes]]. In [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], Leia Organa Solo had to restrain Han Solo from throwing it at a very annoying [[pendulum clock]].

The planet Coruscant's [[New Jedi Temple]] contained a meeting chamber for the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] that bore larmalstone flooring.<ref name="Vortex">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Vortex]]''</ref>

